# Changelog: researching-github

## 2024-12-30 - Add Prioritization Algorithm

**Update Type:** Feature addition (scoring formula)

**Changes:**
- Added weighted prioritization algorithm to Phase 3 with research-backed weights:
  - Popularity (stars): 40%
  - Maintenance (days since commit): 35%
  - Forks: 15%
  - Issue Health (fewer open issues): 10%
- Created references/prioritization-algorithm.md with:
  - Full normalization formulas for each component
  - Worked example (uber-go/ratelimit: score 0.60)
  - Edge case handling (new repos, archived repos, 0 issues)
  - Customization guidance for different use cases
  - Research basis citing npms.io, GitHub trending, Snyk Advisor
- Updated Phase 6 output format to include scores in repository listings
- Maintains line count under 500 (currently ~500 after additions)

**Rationale:**
Research into npms.io (35% maintenance, 35% popularity), GitHub trending (velocity-based), and Snyk Advisor (maintenance = popularity) shows professional ranking systems weight maintenance equal to or higher than popularity. Our weights prioritize stars slightly higher (40%) since GitHub repos lack download metrics.

**Line Count Impact:** +29 lines in SKILL.md (471 ‚Üí 500), detailed content in references/

