## 2024-12-30 - Initial Creation

**RED Phase Documentation:**

Gap identified: No systematic GitHub research workflow in the researching-skills router. When asked to find GitHub repositories, code patterns, or issues, Claude would:
- Use generic WebSearch without detecting gh CLI availability
- Miss quality assessment framework (stars, license, activity, docs)
- Skip dual-tool strategy (gh CLI primary, web fallback)
- Not follow structured 6-phase workflow

**Skill Details:**
- **Category:** skill-library/claude/skill-management
- **Type:** Process/Pattern
- **Location:** Library (sibling to researching-arxiv, researching-codebase, researching-context7, researching-web)

**Key Features:**
- 6-phase workflow (Environment & Query ‚Üí Search ‚Üí Filter ‚Üí Inspect ‚Üí Extract ‚Üí Synthesize)
- Dual-tool strategy (gh CLI primary with web fallback)
- Quality indicators (‚úÖ High Quality, ‚ö†Ô∏è Medium, üîç Evaluate, ‚ùå Skip)
- Durable code references (function signatures, not line numbers)
- Structured synthesis with citations

